<br>
He looks for the barmaid and says &quot;Lass, if ye'd be so kind, get me th' stong'st ale ye got, and pour one for all the lads 'n'n lasses here as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ever since Waylin had learned what had happened in the last attack in the war against the Lady Vox and her horde, he has not been sleeping. The circles around his eyes makes him look 42 instead of 22. <br>
<br>
&quot;Justice is desreving&quot;, Waylin thinks to himself. &quot;Strength and weapons are nice, but without th' spirits to back them up, they are nothing. The Tribunal will get its revenge and bring th' Lass to Justice. And I will be the one leading that charge with the spirits behind me. Alas, first thing is first though. Celebration, for tommorow we start wiping out the wretched dogs of Blackburrow.&quot;<br>
<br>
The barmaid brings Waylin his ale after she has served everyone else. Walin gives the barmaid the cost of the drinks, and then tips her 10 coins that look almost like silver, but much more rare.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank ye lass. Ye are a kind one. If ye keep th' ales coming to me 'n' the others here, Ill make that tip in th' 100 of those.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udrixa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drixa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Barmaid</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/18/01 12:29:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Justice, one step at a time</span><hr size=1> Drixa  perks up.  Men that tip largely before several stong ales or a few timed wiggles are a rare breed indeed.  She rushes to keep  his ale filled even before it reaches half empty and keeps a mental tab of filling the other drinks to add to his   tab later.  She only hopes he's not off to such a battle in the morning that assures death, as she's seen this kind of behaviour then as well and he seems like such a good lad.... <p>Drixa<BR>
Barmaid of the Hero Heart Tavern<BR>
"Pull up a stool, here's an ale to wash the road dust from your throat, and tell me <I>allllllllll</I> about it..."
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulyndayasoulmender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyndaya Soulmender</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/25/01 12:01:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Justice, one step at a time</span><hr size=1> By looking in the barmaid's eyes Waylin can tell what she is thinking.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nay lass, no glorious battles for me. Though I do not doubt they will come up. For life is a battle, and in th' end ye lose to the foe known as death. But all is not lost fer that is where Justice comes in. Justice is an equlaizer, for if ye die thsoe who care seek justice and justice is normally served.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that Waylin stands mutters something in his native barbarian tounge and disappears.<br>
